cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about an automated system for recommending CNN models for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves evaluating the complexity of the classification task and the classification ability of the CNN model, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper may involve optimization techniques for selecting the optimal CNN model, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may involve information retrieval techniques for evaluating the performance of the CNN models, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
